article.headline: Iona 95, Canisius 58
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Steve Burtt scored 31 points and Kiril Wachsmann added 18 to lead Iona to a 95-58 win over Canisius on Friday night. Marvin McCullough also passed for 10 assists for the Gaels (16-4, 10-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic). The Golden Griffins (5-15, 4-8) opened the game with an 11-2 run but the Gaels bounced back. Burtt hit a 3-pointer with 7 minutes left in the first half to give Iona a 25-23 lead. The Gaels scored 29 of the last 37 points of the half to take a 45-31 lead at the break. Darnell Wilson had 17 points and Corey Herring scored 11 of his 14 points in the first half for Canisius.
